records.Primary image caption: Within the papers of the late Emeritus Professor A.P. Elkin lies an early plan of the township of Morpeth. The construction materials of the extant buildings are identified as Red for brick, Yellow for stone, and Green for wood.

records.Title: Remnants of civilisation
records.Primary image caption: In the dry creek bed of the ephemeral Evelyn Creek lays this ute wreck. It has clearly been deserted for some time and the owner has long since moved on. We dont know where it was first abandoned, or even why. All we know is that flash flooding swept it along the creek bed, scoured the paintwork and left it wedged at a quirky angle between the creek bank and a gum tree. A covering of scrub acts to partially conceal and protect what remains. It may have once been used for station work, but more recently marksmen have used it for target practice, pock-marking bullet holes all over it.

records.Title: Ballets Russes competition photo gallery
records.Primary image caption: My brother, David, and I are dressed in fancy dress for a function at school. It was my last year in Infants School before I went on to Primary School. My mother had made both our outfits. She wasn't a particularly good sewer but I think she has done a pretty good job. I was supposed to be Little Bo Peep, but I seem to have lost my sheep. My outfit was made completely out of crepe paper and Mum had gone to a great deal of trouble in making the hooped skirt and pantaloons. I recall I hated the outfit and didn't want to wear it and much preferred David's Superman costume. It brings back fond memories as my Mum died in 2009 and I miss her greatly. We used this photo in a collage that we put together for her 90th birthday.

records.Primary image caption: Judges comments: FROZEN IN FLIGHT is an amazing photograph that has captured an insect in flight.The image captures the viewers imagination as one endeavours to interpret the content within the photograph.Due to the images soft focus, we can only assume that this insect is a butterfly.The photographer has use a slow shutter speed to capture the movement of the insects wings whilst having the ability to keep the body in sharp focus. The colours within the photograph compliment each other and the blurred background keeps your focus on the main subject being the butterfly. The subject is position nicely in the frame that assists in providing the concept of flight and movement. The overall technique used has allowed this image to be bought to life. Overall an amazing image that is pleasant to view.
